title: Dweeb
lyrics:
Too dumb, too small
To feel the fall
Do you recall when she was something beautiful?
I don't, not at all
(Giving up for you)

I do, I do, I do

I do, I do, I do



Too fair inside

To see the signs

Do you recall the rush you once saw in his eyes?

I don't, another life

A trade for daydreams sold

To have and never hold



I do, I do, I do

I do, I do, I do

I'm giving up for you

I do, I do, I do

I do, ye-ah

Giving up for you

I do, I do, I, do

Giving up for you

I do, I do, I, do

I'm giving up for (giving up for you)

I do, I do, I do
